-- BP relief well 7 days ahead but still aims mid-August
-- 
-- Tue Jul 6, 2010 4:40pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/07/06/us-oil-spill-briefing-idUSTRE6654RZ20100706

 

 HOUSTON  (Reuters) - The first of two relief wells is 7 days ahead of schedule but officials still are targeting mid-August for intercepting and killing BP's blown-out oil well, the U.S. spill incident commander said on Tuesday. 

 (Reporting by  Bruce Nichols , Editing by Sandra Maler)